	<div class="post-content user-defined-markup">
					<p>Hi Cheesie,</p>
<p>Just to follow up on Clumps reply. If you wish to take a look at the range of various titles from Macmillan <strong><a target="_blank" title="just click this link" href="http://be.macmillan.org.uk/be/showsection.aspx?SectionID=448&amp;SEName=downloadable-pdf-files&amp;ProductTypeFilterID=144">just click this link</a></strong>.</p>
<p>There is a very good one titled &#39;<strong><a target="_blank" title="When Someone Close To You Has Cancer" href="http://be.macmillan.org.uk/Downloads/CancerInformation/LivingWithAndAfterCancer/MAC14292SomeonecloseE01.pdf">When Someone Close To You Has Cancer</a></strong>&#39; you could start with.</p>
<p>Take care, G n&#39; J</p><div style="clear:both;"></div>
