	<div class="post-content user-defined-markup">
					<p>On a more practical note from my last post; my sister in law has been an invaluable help during my treatment in the following ways which may be of help: listening without making any suggestions about how I should be feeling or what I should do, made meals for myself and my family, come and cleaned, come round at the crack of dawn to get my boys ready for school when myself and my husband had to head off early on our long trek to hospital appointments, been on the end of text messages, helped passing on information to those I would want to know and filtering it from those I wouldn&#39;t. Basically just non judgementaly be there for her and take your lead from her. Look for practical ways you can help whilst at the same time being aware if she just wants space and to do things for herself. And definitely encourage her to join this community.</p><div style="clear:both;"></div>
					</div>

	



	  
