											</span>
				</td>
				<td class="post-author-user-cell fiji-post-author-user-cell evolution2-post-author-user-cell">
				   <div class="user-name-post-date fiji-user-name-post-date evolution2-user-name-post-date">
						Posted by <span class="user-name">
															<a class="internal-link view-user-profile" href="/members/grogg">
									<span></span>Grogg
								</a>
													</span>
						<div class="post-date">
							<span class="label">
																	<a href="/cancer_types/breast-cancer/f/38/t/100606">on</a>
															</span>
							<span class="value"><a href='/cancer_types/breast-cancer/f/38/p/100606/824561#824561' class="internal-link view-post">30 Oct 2015 11:19 AM</a></span>
						</div>
																	</div>
				</td>
			</tr>
		</table>
	</div>
	
	
	<div class="post-content user-defined-markup">
					<p>I love the chatty texts and sometimes I even remember to reply lol!&nbsp; I didn&#39;t get to sleep till 5am and back up at 8am due to builders in the house.&nbsp; I had a text from a friend saying again&nbsp;he was sorry he had to cancel lunch today etc. I knew lunch was cancelled as he had rung a few days before but in my head I had replied to yesterday&#39;s text but I hadn&#39;t.&nbsp;&nbsp; So don&#39;t be offended if your text isn&#39;t replied to promptly, it&#39;s just sometimes we forget we didn&#39;t type out our reply and press send!!!</p>
<p>I have had sleep issues from day 1 and in the end I had to say something to a close relative who texted me about 7.30am everyday to say &quot;did you sleep last night&quot;.&nbsp; The urge to say &quot;NO I F&#39;G DIDN&#39;T&quot; was just getting too great!.</p>
<p>Someone else suggested something that I too found useful, one person to pass on &quot;news&quot;.&nbsp; i.e. when I was waiting/recovering from surgery my daughter used to take my phone and send a stock message to my friends.&nbsp; She would directly keep family up to date.&nbsp; Perhaps you could ask your SIL if she would like you to do this sometimes it&#39;s a bit overwhelming having to repeat yourself.</p>
<p>I also utilised group messages on Facebook to tell friends where I was at as you know they want to know what treatment is coming up/finishing but don&#39;t like to ask so I would pre-empt and say &quot;going in for surgery Monday, should be home same day, feeling okay and just want to get this stage over with&quot;.&nbsp; </p>
<p>I use FB a lot but I have never posted statuses about my diagnosis or treatment but I know other&#39;s find it helpful to do so.&nbsp; People obviously know me well as they never public posted on my wall asking how I was or saying &quot;well done&quot; etc.&nbsp; as I dislike attention.</p>
<p>Anyway fellow BC battlers.&nbsp; I have a bit of an awkward situation.&nbsp; One of my neighbours has been in quite a lot looking at my building work as they are making similar changes and she hasn&#39;t yet asked why I&#39;m off work.&nbsp; Not sure if it&#39;s twigged with her that I have been off for 5 months!&nbsp; I&#39;m now feeling a bit anxious that she will suddenly ask and when I tell her she will go in to OMG mode.&nbsp; I feel I&#39;ve passed the stage of telling people and dealing with their reactions but I don&#39;t want to lie.&nbsp; Should I just tell her?&nbsp; I don&#39;t want my husband to tell her as I know next time I see her there will be an elephant in the room until someone mentions the C word!</p>
<p></p>
<p></p>
<p></p>
<p></p><div style="clear:both;"></div>
					</div>

	



	  
